GE Aviation Capital Orders 75 Boeing 737 Max 8 Jets Worth $8.25 Billion
Jan 4 17
GE Capital Aviation Services has ordered 75 Boeing 737 Max 8 airplanes. Booked in December, the order is worth $8.25 billion at list prices, though big commercial airplane buyers like GECAS typically enjoy discounts of as much as 50% from Boeing. There was no word on delivery dates for the aircraft, which are all made in Chicago-based Boeing's Renton 737 plant.


